it software for global airline customers, defined product strategy and consortium-driven roadmaps, ran on-site consulting engagements to optimize system usage, business processes, and user experience, and monitored SLA KPIs for airlines including Malaysia Airlines, Vistara, Icelandair, Luxair, Wideroe, and South African Airways. She also led multiple pre-sales initiatives including RFP and RFI responses, workshops, live demos, and value propositions. Earlier, as Product Manager for e-Commerce and Shopping (2006–2013), she led B2C airline web and mobile products with millions of monthly users, defined vision and value propositions for travel search engines, redesigned online banking platforms, built UX customization portfolios, and conducted market research for business cases.  Julia holds a PhD in Computational Mechanics from École des Mines de Paris and an Engineer’s Diploma in Computer Science from Bauman Moscow State Technical University. She has received awards including First Prize at Startup Weekend (Google for Startups, Monaco), an Award for Excellence in Engineering Computations (Emerald Publishing, UK), and an international PhD scholarship (Egide, France).  Her skill set spans AI, ML, GenAI, LLMs, MCPs, RAG, prompt engineering, evaluations, vector databases and embeddings, AWS, Bedrock, SageMaker, MLOps, CLI tools, Python, SQL, ETL, BI tools (Tableau, QuickSight), C/C++, Java, HTML, APIs, XML, JSON, Postman, GitHub, CI/CD, Jira, SAFe and Agile frameworks, CMMI, UX design, PCI DSS, and GDPR. She is fluent in French, English, and Russian, with conversational Spanish.
